1
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:09,360
Has Yaoyang never told you

2
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:11,840
how you were created?

3
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:13,360
I...

4
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:15,720
I was

5
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:18,400
created?

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,840
Yaoyang used a secret art
of the Shadow Clan

7
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:25,440
to create you from a fragment of

8
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,160
my junior sister's immortal soul.

9
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:32,120
That's why

10
00:00:32,120 --> 00:00:33,640
you look exactly like her.

11
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:35,720
No.

12
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:37,800
No.

13
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:40,400
No way.

14
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,720
That can't be.

15
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:43,680
You're lying.

16
00:00:44,040 --> 00:00:45,000
This isn't real.

17
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:46,520
This can't be real.

18
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:47,840
It can't be true!

19
00:00:48,760 --> 00:00:50,960
I have to get the truth from him!

20
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:03,640
If you dare lie to me,

21
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:04,840
I will

22
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:05,720
kill you!

23
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:08,760
[Immortal Beyond Dust]
[Episode 7]

24
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:29,720
Mind and spirit as one.

25
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:32,960
Breath follows its course.

26
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,520
Separate yet connected.

27
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:38,080
Unshaken by changes.

28
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,680
Immortal and mortal merge.

29
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,360
Purify the mind and focus the spirit.

30
00:01:59,000 --> 00:01:59,880
What did you call me?

31
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,560
Master.

32
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,200
I'm not your master.

33
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:07,000
Don't call me that again.

34
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:08,840
So

35
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:12,800
you wouldn't let me call you master

36
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,600
because

37
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:18,920
I'm just a replacement
for your own master.

38
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,120
It seems to be missing a moon.

39
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:35,720
You mustn't take this off.

40
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:38,760
Why?

41
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,560
It's a treasure.

42
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:49,120
Wear it,

43
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:51,240
and no villain will trouble you.

44
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,360
It's Ruoxi.

45
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,160
Ruoxi.

46
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,000
Ruoxi.

47
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,360
Are you alright?

48
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,720
Are you hurt anywhere?

49
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:44,760
Ruoxi,

50
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,760
why aren't you saying anything?

51
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,120
Are you hurt?

52
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:48,960
Let me see.

53
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,440
Don't touch me.

54
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:02,920
You're hurt.

55
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,320
Let's go home.

56
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,560
Let me check on her.

57
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:58,960
How is she?

58
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:00,480
She's injured because of the clash

59
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,760
between the fiendish
and immortal auras inside her.

60
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:03,640
But it's nothing serious.

61
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,920
You should take care of her.

62
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,600
Give this to her

63
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:18,000
when she wakes up.

64
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:20,360
She hates bitter stuff.

65
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:21,760
Give her a piece of candy

66
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:23,840
after she drinks it.

67
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,200
Of all the challenges in the world,

68
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:53,360
love is the hardest.

69
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:55,520
They make quite a good match.

70
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,640
You're awake.

71
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:22,440
Tu Jing.

72
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:26,280
Here.

73
00:06:27,260 --> 00:06:27,840
Drink this.

74
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,640
It'll help you recover faster.

75
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,640
Where did you go?

76
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,640
What happened?

77
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,760
If you don't want to talk about it,

78
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,400
you don't have to.

79
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:06,960
With me,

80
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,840
you can just be yourself.

81
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:44,360
I only found these wild vegetables.

82
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,240
See if you want to
add more anything else.

83
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,720
You want me to cook mushrooms?

84
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,680
That's not what I meant.

85
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,920
I'll kill you!

86
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,440
Last dish.

87
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:01,960
Egg drop soup.

88
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,360
What a feast.

89
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,160
You're injured.

90
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,520
I made you a special meal

91
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,160
to help you recover.

92
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:17,760
Delicious.

93
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:23,320
What is this?

94
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,080
It's Beggar's Chicken.

95
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,560
Beggar's Chicken?

96
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,400
How do you eat this?

97
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:36,360
It's a bit hot.

98
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,840
Better cut it with a knife.

99
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,760
I'll just take it to the kitchen
to handle it.

100
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,400
Oh right,

101
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,520
shouldn't we have some wine
with Beggar's Chicken?

102
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:54,760
Sounds good.

103
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,600
I haven't had a drink in a long time.

104
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,200
No.

105
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,400
You're not fully recovered yet.

106
00:08:58,540 --> 00:08:59,400
You can't drink.

107
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:01,720
I know what my body can handle.

108
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:02,560
Go get it.

109
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:12,280
Here.

110
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,040
Stop drinking.

111
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:25,640
Let go of me.

112
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:26,720
Stop drinking.

113
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,520
Let go.

114
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:39,440
Stop drinking.

115
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:40,560
Let go!

116
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,160
Where is the Shadow Moon Pendant
I gave you?

117
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:49,920
I threw it away.

118
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,200
Where did you throw it?

119
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,840
Can't remember.

120
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,120
Haven't I told you

121
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,000
it is important?

122
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:55,960
Why did you throw it away?

123
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,000
I didn't like it.

124
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,000
Am I not allowed

125
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:01,320
to throw away what I don't like?

126
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:02,360
You...

127
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:36,360
♪What is flickering?♪

128
00:10:36,580 --> 00:10:39,100
♪Shining, delicate, and bright♪

129
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:45,100
♪Like a trace of bitterness in a smile♪

130
00:10:45,140 --> 00:10:47,980
♪What is falling?♪

131
00:10:48,420 --> 00:10:51,220
♪Clean, precise, and light♪

132
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:56,660
♪Like enduring too many farewells♪

133
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:59,180
♪When petals drift down♪

134
00:10:59,220 --> 00:11:00,680
♪When the rain falls all around♪

135
00:11:00,780 --> 00:11:03,380
♪I gaze into your eyes♪

136
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:05,240
♪Beyond the dunes♪

137
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:06,620
♪No end in sight♪

138
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:09,620
♪I am like a mayfly♪

139
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:11,180
♪I won't ask what the future holds♪

140
00:11:11,220 --> 00:11:12,680
♪Nor will I run away♪

141
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:15,640
♪Through all seasons by my side♪

142
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:20,900
♪Searching for sparks in the dust♪

143
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:37,960
♪What is flickering?♪

144
00:11:38,180 --> 00:11:40,660
♪Shining, delicate, and bright♪

145
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:46,660
♪Like a trace of bitterness in a smile♪

146
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,900
♪What is falling?♪

147
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:52,840
♪Clean, precise, and light♪

148
00:11:53,060 --> 00:11:58,060
♪Like enduring too many farewells♪

149
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:00,660
♪When petals drift down♪

150
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:02,160
♪When the rain falls all around♪

151
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:04,820
♪I gaze into your eyes♪
